Nigerian fast-rising singer and songwriter, Moses Felix Ofegor, popularly known as S.K.Y-HB, is set to release his highly anticipated single, “Boss Boss” on April 23, 2022. The single is a vibrant blend of Afrobeats and sub-genre that reflects heavily on youthful exuberance, culture, love and growth. The project will showcase his versatility and preach love through music. It will also give an insight on his personality. The single is an honest reflection of his story and painting his own portrait as opposed to conforming. The song (Boss Boss) talks about his love for popular signer, Davido and affirming the fact that Davido is a real ‘Boss Boss’ S.K.Y-HB, whose real name is Moses Felix Ofegor, was born on October 1, 1998 to thefFamily of Mr and Mrs Ogidigbo Moses a native of Emevor Isoko North LGA of Delta State, Speaking with our correspondent, S.K.Y-HB said, “I started doing music when I was 11 year-old but I wasn’t serious about it.” He professionally took up a career in music in the late 2021 when he joined JSL NATION, an artist management and music promotiona company founded by Mr. Shonde Joseph Olawale, where he released his first debut single, ‘Enter’, which is currently trending on all digital platforms.